ce:section.ce:para:
Specificity is a vital metric for assessing analytical performance. It verified whether our probe proposed could be effectively differentiate similar oligonucleotides. We employed miRNA-141 and miRNA-21 about non-base-mismatched (Mis-0), double-base-mismatched (Mis-2), four-base-mismatched (Mis-4), five-base-mismatched (Mis-5) and miRNA-145 to explore in subsequent experiments. Our findings revealed that only the non-base-mismatched miRNA-141 and miRNA-21 led to a conspicuous increase in F/F
                        0, whereas the changes in the presence of other mismatch miRNA or oligonucleotides were negligible (Fig. 5
                        ). These results indicated that the simultaneous detection platform devised in this study possessed considerable selectivity and specificity towards miRNA-141 and miRNA-21 present in an aqueous solution. The investigation into linearity and selectivity demonstrated the practical utility of this approach.
